wikipedia_page.main: Captain Otway Cuffe (11 January 1853 – 3 January 1912) was twice mayor of Kilkenny and a notable person in Kilkenny, founding businesses and organisations to profit the local people.

response: Cuffe was the second son of John Cuffe, 3rd Earl of Desart and his wife, Lady Elizabeth Campbell.  He had an older sister, Lady Alice Mary Cuffe, and brother, William Cuffe, and a younger brother, Captain Otway Cuffe.  His older sister married John Henniker-Major, 5th Baron Henniker and was the mother of twelve children.
* 1809 John Otway Cuffe, 2nd Earl of Desart
